1088,IssuesEvent,2017-11-20 23:49:18+00:00,16331291,davisking/dlib,6259399,davisking,,,closed,CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH is being overwritten,[],[],1,"<!-- ================================================================ -->
<!-- =====================  BUG REPORT TEMPLATE ===================== -->
<!-- ================================================================ -->


<!-- Delete the above instructions and then provide a general summary of the issue in the Title above.  Then fill out the template below. -->

## Expected Behavior
<!--- Tell us what should happen.  What were you doing?  What part of dlib are you using?  What do you think should happen? -->
I want to specify CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH to have find_library, find_path, and find_file look in different locations for libraries, binaries, and headers.  I need to do this because I am developing on a system that does not install its dependencies to /usr/.

## Current Behavior
<!--- Tell us what happens instead of the expected behavior.  If you get an error, include the entire error message in the bug report.  DO NOT POST SCREEN SHOTS.  Paste in the text instead.   If the issue is some kind of build problem, include the entire CMake output along with the error message. -->
CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH is being overwritten in dlib/cmake_utils/add_python_module line 35, so I can't specify my own CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH via the command-line invocation of cmake.  This should either be removed or changed to append to the CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH, like this: `list(APPEND CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH ""${PYTHON_PATH}"")`
I tried both ways and both worked for me.

## Steps to Reproduce
<!--- Provide an unambiguous set of steps to reproduce this bug. Include code to reproduce, if relevant -->
Put dependencies (like boost and openblas) into non-standard directories, pass `-DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/path/to/your/deps` to cmake, and build using the CMakeLists.txt in dlib/tools/python so that add_python_module is called.  /path/to/your/deps should be the directory that contains the libs/, bin/, and include/ directories.


* **Version**: <!-- What version of dlib? --> v19.7
* **Where did you get dlib**: <!-- Did you get it from an official source like dlib.net, this github repo, or somewhere else? --> git clone -b 'v19.7' --single-branch https://github.com/davisking/dlib.git dlib/
* **Platform**: <!-- include something like `lsb_release -a` output, or if Windows, version and 32-bit or
  64-bit --> Ubuntu 16.04.3 within a Docker container (version 17.09.0-ce)
* **Compiler**: <!-- What compiler are you using?  What version of that compiler? --> GCC 5.4.0
",{},{}
