1428,IssuesEvent,2018-08-13 09:26:46+00:00,96006529,cmorisse/ikp3db,544433,cmorisse,,,closed,Why doesn't ikp3db exit when program exists with no exit code?,[],[],7,"Been experimenting a little with `ikp3db` on Cloud9 and was just curious as to why does it make sense to keep `ikp3db` running even after the program being debugged exists [here](https://github.com/cmorisse/ikp3db/blob/3b89dde87cb90db700dd97232861e35e113e6b9d/ikp3db.py#L1867)? `ikp3db` seems to normally exist with the same exit code as the program when one is given [here](https://github.com/cmorisse/ikp3db/blob/3b89dde87cb90db700dd97232861e35e113e6b9d/ikp3db.py#L1882) and in this case there's no exit code, but is it reasonable to expect every program to explicitly exit with some status code? Does it indeed make sense to keep `ikp3db` running here instead of simply defaulting to an exit code of `0`?

Thank you!",{},{}
