2150,IssuesEvent,2015-10-05 18:01:33+00:00,9289343,svinota/pyroute2,1132557,tomislacker,,,opened,[Docs] Explain filter flags for IP/subnets,[],[],0,"The [`IPRouteMixin.tc()` method](../blob/84f99fbbce049517300a08c0389bf27765e1e4f6/pyroute2/iproute.py#L777) has good documentation for most components but is a bit lacking on the bitwise math necessary to create a valid filter.  For example, the following snippet:

> ```py
> # two filters: one to load packets into 1:10 and the
> # second to 1:20
> ip.tc(""add-filter"", ""u32"", eth0,
>       parent=0x10000,
>       prio=10,
>       protocol=socket.AF_INET,
>       target=0x10010,
>       keys=[""0x0006/0x00ff+8"", ""0x0000/0xffc0+2""])
> ip.tc(""add-filter"", ""u32"", eth0,
>       parent=0x10000,
>       prio=10,
>       protocol=socket.AF_INET,
>       target=0x10020,
>       keys=[""0x5/0xf+0"", ""0x10/0xff+33""])
> ```

It may not be clear to most users how to compose the `keys` argument or even what the example `keys` arguments are describing.",{},{}
2162,IssuesEvent,2017-09-11 01:46:18+00:00,18892209,tartley/colorama,1650862,liangxin1300,,,opened,colorama and readline in python3,[],[],0,"Hi:
    I have a problem when using colorama and readline in python3.
    This is the example code:
 
    `from readline import set_history_length
     from colorama import init
     from colorama import Fore
     init()
     input(Fore.RED+'Please input: ')`


then, when the input length is very long(longer than term width), next input contents will **overwrite
the head in the same line**.

drop the line
`from readline import set_history_length`
