2261,IssuesEvent,2017-02-15 04:19:54+00:00,41179827,Rapptz/discord.py,1695103,Rapptz,,,closed,"Check for heartbeat acknowledgements, timeout if they are absent.","[{'id': 251130941, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Rapptz/discord.py/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"It is possible (and unfortunately not uncommon) for websocket connections to close in such a way that the client never sees the websocket connection close, and ""successfully"" sends messages into the void, but never receives any responses. The client should check that heartbeats are being acknowledged in a timely fashion, and consider the connection dead if they are not (and attempt a reconnect).",{},{}
