2357,IssuesEvent,2016-01-08 03:32:18+00:00,5934517,dpkp/kafka-python,843444,dpkp,,,closed,The parallel model of MultiConsumer ,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dpkp/kafka-python/labels/consumer', 'name': 'consumer', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],1,"It seems to me the parallel model of current MultiConsumer is that multiple child processes fetch messages to a centralized queue, and then the parent process dispatches the messages from this queue to the application via MultiConsumer.get_messages() API. 

I was wondering whether there is any provision in current code to support another kind of parallel model where the parent process fetches messages into a queue and multiple child processes dispatches the messages from this queue to application? The reason is that in our application, the processing of each message is CPU-intensive, so we want to have multiple processes to processing the messages.",{},{}
