2406,IssuesEvent,2018-04-25 22:43:33+00:00,11974348,evansd/whitenoise,46198,aeby,,,closed,Allow multiple roots,[],[],2,"Would it make sense/is a PR welcome to allow multiple ""root"" folders in the Django middleware? Right now the files in the directory specified by `WHITENOISE_ROOT` is served at `/`. I think of a setting like this:

```
# Keep this setting for backward compatibility
WHITENOISE_ROOT = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'if/dist')

# Roots as tuples of <DIRECTORY>, <PREFIX> 
WHITENOISE_ROOTS = (
    (<MY_OTHER_DIR>, '/other/'),
    (<MY_PWA_DIR>, '/pwa/')
)
```
In [middleware.py](https://github.com/evansd/whitenoise/blob/master/whitenoise/middleware.py#L41) we could allow other roots with something like this:

```
for root in self.roots:
    add_files(*root)
```
The motivation behind are PWA with service workers that need to be served from a specific directory due to scoping. If I have for example an app running at /pwa i have to serve its service worker from this directory.",{},{}
2407,IssuesEvent,2016-07-17 20:52:42+00:00,11974348,evansd/whitenoise,19630,evansd,,,closed,middleware order,[],[],1,"The documentation says to place whitenoise middleware above all others apart from Django's SecurityMiddleware (http://whitenoise.evans.io/en/stable/django.html#enable-whitenoise).  That works for [1.9 when it's at the top](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.9/topics/http/middleware/) but [1.8 puts it at the bottom](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.8/topics/http/middleware/).

I don't know if security can be put at the top for 1.8, or if the docs need more clarification here.",{},{}
