3063,IssuesEvent,2017-12-02 06:39:41+00:00,36919582,thisbejim/Pyrebase,5833990,ininex,,,closed,Streaming: If you want to check a stream thread exists,[],[],0,"One critical feature that Pyrebase miss is to mark running thread of stream. In some scenarios, ""stream_id"" is not enough. For example, if I want to prevent duplicated stream threads from being generated at same database path, system needs to make decision before stream handler is being called(I believe in current design stream_id is only returned as stream handler input, which is not useful in this case). Sometimes you need to close the stream or do logical check at other places where you cannot access original SSE client reference. What you need to do is simply adding ""name"" property to stream thread, subclass ""Stream"" class in ""pyrebase"" and override ""start"" with following code:

`   
def start(self):
self.thread = threading.Thread(target=self.start_stream, name={any_name_you_prefer})
self.thread.start()
return self
`

Then, subclass ""Database"" in ""pyrebase"", override function ""stream"" so it will finally returns your customized Stream subclass.

To retrieve the stream thread from other places, simply:

`       
for thread in threading.enumerate():
            if thread.name == {any_name_you_prefer}:
            ... 
`",{},{}
