4007,IssuesEvent,2017-03-29 22:50:40+00:00,120894,michaeljones/breathe,425260,eric-wieser,,,opened,BUG: Anonymous namespaces do not work,[],[],0,"For something like the following `myfile.cpp`, with `EXTRACT_ANON_NSPACES   = YES`:

```c++
//! My internals
namespace {
    //! My var
    int x;
}
```
Doxygen generates a namespace called `anonymous_namespace{myfile.cpp}`. This works alright, and can be included with

```
.. doxygennamespace:: anonymous_namespace{myfile.cpp}
```

However, this means that sphinx ends up getting passed something akin to:

```
.. c:data:: p32_i2c&amp; anonymous_namespace{myfile.cpp}::x;
```

Which it chokes on.

",{},{}
