6182,IssuesEvent,2015-04-25 17:16:54+00:00,1576129,KristianOellegaard/django-hvad,5879675,spectras,,,closed,Support for multi-table inheritance,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/KristianOellegaard/django-hvad/labels/new%20feature', 'name': 'new feature', 'color': '009800'}]",[],3,"I couldn't find anything in the docs so I don't know what's the supposed status of this, but from what I experienced, multi-table inheritance doesn't work. Suppose you have the following model:

```python
class BaseBook(TranslatableModel):
    translations = TranslatedFields(
        name=models.CharField(max_length=100)
    )

class Book(BaseBook):
    chapters = models.IntegerField()
```

Hvad will complain:
```
django.core.exceptions.ImproperlyConfigured: No TranslatedFields found on <class 'demo.models.Book'>, subclasses of TranslatableModel must define TranslatedFields.
```

And if you define `TranslatedFields`, you then get an error:
```
django.core.exceptions.FieldError: Local field 'language_code' in class 'BookTranslation' clashes with field of similar name from base class 'BaseBookTranslation'
```

It would be nice to have support for this, although I have no idea how difficult it would be to implement. And if the effort to achieve this is too important, I guess a note should be added to the docs.",{},{}
