8304,IssuesEvent,2017-12-09 22:50:21+00:00,2625205,robotframework/SeleniumLibrary,2665023,aaltat,574284,robotframework,opened,Add option to start browser headless in Open Browser keyword,[],[],0,"Add support for Firefox and Chrome to start with headless mode in `Open Browser` keyword. The headless is quite common need within the user base of the SeleniunLibrary. The headless can be done, by using the `Create WebDirver` keyword but the code in the Robot Framework data is quite horrible. With the Selenium 3.8.0 it is easy to modify the `Open Browser` to support headless mode with Firefox and Chrome. ",{},{}
