8322,IssuesEvent,2016-06-08 19:25:38+00:00,2625205,robotframework/Selenium2Library,2665023,aaltat,574284,robotframework,closed,Allowing rebot to process Report and Log for acceptance tests when using --dryrun,[],[],7,"See PR #535

In a more global PR for robotframework, I plan to use the ```--dryrun``` option in rebot to be accepted and give relevant results.

For now this allows running the acceptance tests with the ```--dryrun``` option and obtain the Report and Log files.

In this PR, it is also changed to ```include_root_package_name = True``` in run_unit_tests.py which is critical for me in my Linux machine (and harmless in Windows).",{},{}
