9211,IssuesEvent,2016-07-05 07:43:26+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,BibDocFile-level restriction,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_BibDocFile', 'name': 'c_BibDocFile', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_global', 'name': 'c_global', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"Originally on 2011-05-27

It would be nice to be able to restrict a specific format of a `BibDocFile`. 

Take e.g. the use case of multimedia handling, where a master video is uploaded and slaves are created. Now both master and slaves are related to the same content, and therefore, because of the `bibdocfile` philosophy they should belong to the same `BibDoc`. However, a common policy might impose that the master should be restricted, while the slaves should be public.

Currently this is only possible by either assigning the master to a different `BibDoc` (hence with a different `docname`) or by setting the `HIDDEN` flag to the master format. The latter solution is not ideal, because the master would not be streamable anymore.

An even more granular solution is therefore envisaged. 

The near-future `BibDocMoreInfo` refactoring by Piotr (where this class will become a generic container of properties, either at the `BibDoc` level or at the `BibDocFile` level) will possibly handle it as yet a new `BibDocFile` property.",{},{}
9212,IssuesEvent,2016-07-04 12:24:40+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,WebStyle: gap between header menu and search box,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebStyle', 'name': 'c_WebStyle', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_bug', 'name': 't_bug', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"Originally by *jpcorral* on 2011-08-19

This problem appears in INSPIRE (not CDS). Using a very long query the page loads with enough space to show the query but due to the `visibility: hidden;` CSS property in the following classes it is not displayed to the user: `navtrailbox, navtrailboxbody, navtrail`

This creates a gap between the header menu and the search box. `display: none;` would be a better property to use as it would not reserve the space on the page and the query will not be shown.

An alternative suggestion is; If the HTML code for the query is not needed then do not send it to client. This could be done by removing the table with the class `navtrailbox`.

For example: http://tinyurl.com/longqueryinspire",{},{}
9213,IssuesEvent,2015-07-21 09:17:01+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,582735,egabancho,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,Accepting metadata contribution from Drupal,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_global', 'name': 'c_global', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_major', 'name': 'p_major', 'color': 'e11d21'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/s_CDS', 'name': 's_CDS', 'color': '4D94CE'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"Originally on 2011-06-27

In a recent integration between CDS(Invenio) and *Drupal* at CERN, a new BibFormat output format has been created, called **XDRUPAL**, that is suitable to easily export typical CDS records (photos with ""tirage""s, movies, publications, preprints, conference contributions).

As suggested, it would be great, to exploit the crowd-sourcing effect, by receiving back from Drupal, optional additional title and description (with a corresponding language information), that can be stored back into the MARC.

For this we can decide to have a new MARC field with the following subfields:

- `$a` the value (coming from Drupal)
* `$b` the intended MARC field (e.g. `245__a` for the title, `520__a` for the abstract)
* `$c` the ""tirage"", i.e. the document identifier in case this is referring to a picuture within the record.
* `$d` the language
* `$9` the author (for provenance, this can be the email address of the author)

------------

The passing of information could be achieved by exploiting the fact that a user enriching a record/tirage already retrieved via XDrupal, can feedback to CDS by being redirected to an authenticated session in CDS already prefilled (by passing any information on the *GET* request) to a form in CDS showing a preview of the picture/record, the contributed title and description, the possibility to choose the language, and where we could clearly state:

""*do you agree to contribute this title and description as a reliable information to be archived together with the original record in CDS, with your name?*"" 

And this could then simply trigger a bibupload.",{},{}
9214,IssuesEvent,2015-04-17 09:46:38+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,517546,tiborsimko,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,"RFC Separate WebAlerts, WebBaskets, and query logging","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebAlert', 'name': 'c_WebAlert', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebBasket', 'name': 'c_WebBasket', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebSearch', 'name': 'c_WebSearch', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/in_triage', 'name': 'in_triage', 'color': 'fef2c0'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/master', 'name': 'master', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_blocker', 'name': 'p_blocker', 'color': 'e11d21'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/RFC', 'name': 'RFC', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/s_CDS', 'name': 's_CDS', 'color': '4D94CE'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],12,"* [ ] Allow user to create alerts based on any query. Alert engine MUST respect user id of creator.
* [ ] Allow creating alerts with different notification backends - email, tags/baskets, web notification.
* [ ] Remove support for `p1`, `f1`, `p2`, `f2`, etc. and use only `p` (`query`) argument (this might be touch also OAI Server).
* [ ] Add notification system that can be used in webhooks (cc @lnielsen-cern)

... More details will come together with #2587 and #2619.

**NOTE** Can we go for fast track with this RFC because it is kind of blocker for new search engine using *Invenio-Query-Parser*.

--
@egabancho @kasioumis @kaplun @tiborsimko @zenodo",{},{}
9217,IssuesEvent,2015-07-27 20:58:30+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,Allow the selection of full and brief format from the WebSearch collection interface,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebSearch', 'name': 'c_WebSearch', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/master', 'name': 'master', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/s_INSPIRE', 'name': 's_INSPIRE', 'color': '207de5'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],7,"Originally on 2010-07-07

(Originally submitted by Ferran Jorba on Savannah: https://savannah.cern.ch/task/?12167)

The tools to create formats (.bft and .py) are powerful and programmer oriented. 
However, there is no easy way to assign those brief and full formats to a given collection. It would be nice to integrate those options to the WebSearch collection definition, like portalboxes, search options and other collection specific preferences. Maybe this could make .bfo files obsolete? 
I understand that HB and HD should be the default, good enough for most collection and sites, and it should remain the valid ones unless a specific choice has been made. 
Please note that this preference should be taken into account also when creating the first, cached page (http://cdsware.cern.ch/repo/?p=cds-invenio.git&a=search&h=HEAD&st=grep&s=def+create_latest_additions_info) ",{},{}
9236,IssuesEvent,2015-03-26 21:29:38+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,119349,kaplun,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,jsonalchemy: Invenio should accept any indicator as valid for any tag,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_general', 'name': 'c_general', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/master', 'name': 'master', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_major', 'name': 'p_major', 'color': 'e11d21'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_bug', 'name': 't_bug', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],6,"Originally on 2014-03-28

A majority of Marc21 tags accept different values for indicators.  Currenty Invenio just uses a restricted subset, mostly empty or undefined values.

When valid Marc21 records from other sources are imported to Invenio, most of the fields are not recognized, because don't fall in this restricted subset.  For example, a title with valid tags and subfields, like:

 245 14 $a The Merchand of Venice

is not recognized as such: it is not displayed, not indexed, not exported.

Given the amount of combinations in Marc21, accepting any indicator as valid is a much better solution than the current behaviour.

The sooner this behaviour is corrected, the better.
",{},{}
