9260,IssuesEvent,2016-06-07 18:00:21+00:00,45115104,inveniosoftware/invenio-rest,1814661,slint,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,views: weak ETags check in ContentNegotiatedMethodView,[],[],0,"When serving gzipped responses configured in nginx, strong ETags added by the backend get automatically converted to weak ones (since the content served technically isn't byte-to-byte equivalent to the original). Because of this, while the application may add a header like `ETag: ""1234""`, nginx converts it to `ETag: ""W/""1234""""`. So when the client asks for the same resource with an `If-None-Match: ""W/""1234"""" header`, the [`ContentNegotiatedMethodView.check_etag`](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-rest/blob/master/invenio_rest/views.py#L217-L247) method fails to validate the ETag, since currently it checks only for [star ETags (""*"") and strong ones by default](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-rest/blob/master/invenio_rest/views.py#L238-L243) and thus doesn't respond with a `SameContentException` (304).

I guess adding a `weak=False` argument in the method and using [`werkzeug.datastractures.ETags.contains_weak`](http://werkzeug.pocoo.org/docs/0.11/datastructures/#werkzeug.datastructures.ETags.contains_weak) for the check, will keep backwards compatibility, and still provide the ability to check for weak ETags when needed.

",{},{}
