9811,IssuesEvent,2015-11-30 12:42:00+00:00,3342046,RDFLib/rdflib,434495,danmichaelo,1401847,RDFLib,opened,Turtle serializer: roundtrip error with prefix relative to base,[],[],0,"Given the following data:

```turtle
@base <http://data.me/> .
@prefix me: <onto#> .

<entity/1> me:acronym ""ABC"" .
```

When doing:

```
g = Graph()
g.load(data, format='turtle')
g.serialize(format='turtle', base='http://data.me/')
```

I get:

```turtle
@prefix me: <http://data.me/onto#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

<entity/1> ns1:acronym ""ABC"" .
```

so the `me` prefix is expanded to `http://data.me/onto#` upon loading, which is good, but not contracted again upon serializing. Also, note that the new `ns1` prefix is not included in the prefix list. 

Here's a ipython notebook with some variations over the same issue:

https://gist.github.com/danmichaelo/ca90e9a88297ecb9af16
",{},{}
