9904,IssuesEvent,2018-04-27 14:53:48+00:00,12629378,gems-uff/noworkflow,327789,JoaoFelipe,1486707,gems-uff,closed,Time precision is not big enough to distinguish versions,[],[],1,"noWorkflow 2 uses the evaluation and member moment to distinguish the version of values. However, the collected time precision is not enough for some evaluations and it seems that there is no way to increase the precision.

We can replace this information by a sequential moment number and all version operations will keep working, but we will lose the actual moment.
Alternatively, we can create a Moment table with the following columns: trial_id, id, datetime, and use the id in this table to identify the moment in evaluations. This imposes an overhead, but keeps the time information.

Which one is the best approach?",{},{}
