10099,IssuesEvent,2016-07-12 16:55:09+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,556268,tagliala,1505683,FortAwesome,closed,Separate brand icons file?,[],[],1,"I work on a few applications that do't really associate with any ""brands"" like there are icons for in FontAwesome. I love all the other icons, but all these brand icons just seem like unnecessary bloat, and I would imagine that's the same case for several others as well.  I mean... it even includes 3 variations of the ""Pied Piper icon which is a logo for fictional company from a TV show... I will never need these!

At the very least perhaps all the brand related icons could just be consolidated into a `scss/_icons-brands.scss` and `less/icons-brands.less` file and i could build my own CSS by including everything except this file. I know the actual icons would still be loaded in the font file, but this would at least reduce my CSS bloat.  I'd be happy to make a PR for this if it was deemed a good idea. ",{},{}
