10402,IssuesEvent,2018-07-11 17:51:27+00:00,3274387,RallyTools/RallyRestToolkitForPython,2688600,pgacv2,1643197,RallyTools,opened,No apparent way to fetch data about closed projects,[],[],0,"`getProjects()` uses `getAccessibleProjects()`, which does not return closed projects. `getProject()` returns `None` if you give it the name of a closed project. [This SO question](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50686756/how-to-get-rally-stories-in-closed-projects-using-pyral) is also about getting user stories from closed projects.

Getting information about closed projects is probably not a common need, but it would be handy when you want to run metrics on old projects.",{},{}
10404,IssuesEvent,2017-11-25 15:44:20+00:00,36320961,beerfactory/hbmqtt,159819,cefn,1656662,beerfactory,opened,Document Last Will and Testament implementation?,[],[],0,"I thought the Last Will and Testament feature of MQTT ( https://www.hivemq.com/blog/mqtt-essentials-part-9-last-will-and-testament ) was not supported by hbmqtt since it wasn't noted in http://hbmqtt.readthedocs.io/en/latest/references/mqttclient.html?highlight=will#reference as part of the allowed keys in the config.

However at the footer of the HBMQTT client implementation the clause ```if ""will"" in self.config:``` suggests that there is in fact support. 

