10556,IssuesEvent,2017-03-22 22:08:48+00:00,15510373,openfisca/openfisca-web-api,12686,cbenz,1794404,openfisca,opened,Handle period mismatch errors,[],[],0,"Follows openfisca/openfisca-france#716

Problem is explained in the referenced issue.

We could catch `ValueError` around [this line](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-web-api/blob/433e8ded43a3669cee577b53b20518a53aa8be79/openfisca_web_api/controllers/calculate.py#L82), but `ValueError` is not enough specific and this could lead to abusive exception catches.

So I suggest introducing a specific exception named `PeriodError` or `PeriodMismatch`, and catch it.

CC @fpagnoux 

Also apply this fix to other `scenario.new_simulation` calls.",{},{}
