Since it uses an external data set [GEO GSE70138](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE70138) (rather than a test contained within cmapPy) it isn't clear, if this error reflects upon an update or problem within cmapPy, the tutorial, or GSE70138. (Besides not being able to follow a tutorial, this error hence makes it difficult for new users to become familiar with gctx files / cmapPy.)

**works: upper part of tutorial**

```python
import pandas as pd
sig_info = pd.read_csv(""GSE70138_Broad_LINCS_sig_info.txt"", sep=""\t"") # updated file name

vorinostat_ids = sig_info[""sig_id""][sig_info[""pert_iname""] == ""vorinostat""]
```



```python
# Let us additionally report on the data
print(""number of samples treated with vorinostat:"", len(vorinostat_ids))
print('\n---- show first ones for debugging ----')
[print(x) for x in vorinostat_ids.values[:5]];
```

