11451,IssuesEvent,2017-02-25 19:25:05+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,399602,cheister,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Pants does not correctly shade Java 9 modular jars or jars with a java class in the top-level package,[],[],0,"In Java 9 modular jars now contain a `module-info.class` file at the the top-level of the package hierarchy.  When Pants shades the classes in the jar it will see the top-level `module-info.class` and generate a [jarjar rule](https://github.com/pantsbuild/jarjar/blob/master/src/main/java/org/pantsbuild/jarjar/help.txt#L44) that will shade all top-level class files.

`rule * __shaded_by_pants__.@1`

When jarjar runs with this rule it will relocate extra string references in the shaded jar that can cause runtime errors.

For example with the pants shaded jar of errorprone 2.0.17 you will get the runtime error

```
java.lang.annotation.AnnotationFormatError: Invalid default: public abstract com.google.errorprone.BugPattern$Suppressibility com.google.errorprone.BugPattern.suppressibility()
 at java.lang.reflect.Method.getDefaultValue(Method.java:612)
 at sun.reflect.annotation.AnnotationType.<init>(AnnotationType.java:128)
 at sun.reflect.annotation.AnnotationType.getInstance(AnnotationType.java:85)
 at sun.reflect.annotation.AnnotationParser.parseAnnotation2(AnnotationParser.java:266)
 at sun.reflect.annotation.AnnotationParser.parseAnnotations2(AnnotationParser.java:120)
 at sun.reflect.annotation.AnnotationParser.parseAnnotations(AnnotationParser.java:72)
 at java.lang.Class.createAnnotationData(Class.java:3521)
 at java.lang.Class.annotationData(Class.java:3510)
 at java.lang.Class.getAnnotation(Class.java:3415)
 at com.google.errorprone.BugCheckerInfo.create(BugCheckerInfo.java:96)
 at com.google.errorprone.scanner.BuiltInCheckerSuppliers.getSuppliers(BuiltInCheckerSuppliers.java:231)
 at com.google.errorprone.scanner.BuiltInCheckerSuppliers.<clinit>(BuiltInCheckerSuppliers.java:260)
 at com.google.errorprone.ErrorProneCompiler$Builder.<init>(ErrorProneCompiler.java:96)
 at com.google.errorprone.ErrorProneCompiler.builder(ErrorProneCompiler.java:91)
 at com.google.errorprone.ErrorProneCompiler.compile(ErrorProneCompiler.java:70)
 at com.google.errorprone.ErrorProneCompiler.main(ErrorProneCompiler.java:49)
 at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method)
 at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(NativeMethodAccessorImpl.java:62)
 at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43)
 at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:498)
 at com.martiansoftware.nailgun.NGSession.run(NGSession.java:280)
```

because the top-level star rule for jarjar will relocate the default values for the `BugPattern$Suppressibility` enum:

```
com.google.errorprone.BugPattern$Suppressibility
	153: ""__shaded_by_pants__/SUPPRESS_WARNINGS""
	157: ""__shaded_by_pants__/CUSTOM_ANNOTATION""
	161: ""__shaded_by_pants__/UNSUPPRESSIBLE""
```

instead of

```
com.google.errorprone.BugPattern$Suppressibility
	153: ""SUPPRESS_WARNINGS""
	157: ""CUSTOM_ANNOTATION""
	161: ""UNSUPPRESSIBLE""
```


The current workaround is to include a shading rule to exclude the top-level package

```
custom_rules=[
  Shader.exclude_package('com.google.errorprone', recursive=True),
  Shading.create_exclude('*'),
]
```

I'm still investigating if this is a bug in jarjar or if pants should not specify the toplevel * rule to jarjar. ",{},{}
11461,IssuesEvent,2015-11-04 16:47:41+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,7378,baroquebobcat,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,`./pants bench` appears to have recently stopped working,[],[],0,"If you run `./pants bench` on any `benchmark` `Target`, `pants` will fail with the following error message:

```
Exception caught:
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/bin/pants_exe.py"", line 122, in <module>
    main()
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/bin/pants_exe.py"", line 116, in main
    _run(exiter)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/bin/pants_exe.py"", line 102, in _run
    result = run()
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/bin/pants_exe.py"", line 86, in run
    return goal_runner.run()
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/bin/goal_runner.py"", line 340, in run
    result = self._execute_engine()
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/bin/goal_runner.py"", line 329, in _execute_engine
    result = engine.execute(self._context, self._goals)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/engine/engine.py"", line 26, in execute
    self.attempt(context, goals)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/engine/round_engine.py"", line 218, in attempt
    goal_executor.attempt(explain)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/engine/round_engine.py"", line 47, in attempt
    task.execute()
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/backend/core/tasks/mutex_task_mixin.py"", line 97, in execute
    return self.execute_for(targets)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/backend/jvm/tasks/benchmark_run.py"", line 107, in execute_for
    workunit_labels=[WorkUnitLabel.RUN])
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/java/util.py"", line 46, in execute_java
    executor = executor or SubprocessExecutor(distribution)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/java/executor.py"", line 178, in __init__
    super(SubprocessExecutor, self).__init__(distribution=distribution)
  File ""/Users/ggonzalez/proj/pants/src/python/pants/java/executor.py"", line 79, in __init__
    .format(distribution))

Exception message: A valid distribution is required, given: None
```

This error seems to have been introduced in 17712e32f4541d6591d2a8fb900809d4391b7e30.  It's easy to verify that this error will always occur because:

* `pants.java.util.execute_java` fails if the `distribution` argument is not supplied and defaults to `None`
* `pants.backend.jvm.tasks.BenchmarkRun.execute_for` calls `execute_java` without supplying the `distribution` argument, so it defaults to `None`",{},{}
