11483,IssuesEvent,2017-03-24 02:50:37+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Create `Tasks` struct before constructing the `Scheduler`,"[{'id': 268094252, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine', 'name': 'engine', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 472006774, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/native', 'name': 'native', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Because the `Tasks` struct is currently created post scheduling, it's necessary to mutate the content of the `Arc` that is holding it. That open up the possibility of a panic, and makes initialization of the `RuleGraph` awkward (as demonstrated on #4371).

Instead, the `Tasks` struct should be constructed independently before the `Scheduler`, and then passed in, so that the `Scheduler` can hold an immutable reference without the `Arc`-mutation loophole. ",{},{}
11486,IssuesEvent,2018-01-23 03:03:01+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,pytest junit xml not written if tests fail,"[{'id': 22426646, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 137550486, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/in-progress', 'name': 'in-progress', 'color': '009800', 'default': False}, {'id': 378083067, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/python', 'name': 'python', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}, {'id': 234031381, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/user%20reported', 'name': 'user reported', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'jsirois', 'id': 157586, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/157586?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jsirois', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"Specifying the --test-pytest-junit-xml-dir flag does not work if the tests fail.

The problem seems to be in pytest_run.py, line 626 (_do_run_tests):
the checked() call raises an ErrorWhileTesting exception if the run fails, thus skipping the rest of the function, including the call to expose_results.

can the call to checked() be removed? The error handling for ErrorWhileTesting in _run_tests just builds a result from the exception which (I think) matches the original result. 

pants version 1.4.0rc0",{},{}
