11540,IssuesEvent,2016-07-12 16:08:27+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,159980,dbentley,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,go_remote_libaries fails if library contains directory with same name as repo,[],[],0,"Example: http://github.com/spf13/cobra also defines a package called ""cobra""

This led us to write a BUILD file like:

```
go_remote_libraries(
  rev='6a8bd97bdb1fc0d08a83459940498ea49d3e8c93',
  packages=[
    '',
    'cobra',
    'cobra/cmd',
    'doc',
  ],
)
```

Which leads to the error message:
```
Exception message: File BuildFile(3rdparty/go/github.com/spf13/cobra/BUILD, FileSystemProjectTree(/Users/dbentley/workspace/source)) defines address 'cobra' more than once.
 Loading addresses from '3rdparty/go/github.com/spf13/cobra' failed.
Invalid BUILD files for [3rdparty/go/github.com/spf13/cobra::]
```

I think this is because the empty string is interpreted as meaning ""package name"", which in this case is also cobra.

This pattern is not exceedingly common, but it's also not bizarre.",{},{}
