11685,IssuesEvent,2016-01-04 19:03:56+00:00,13592924,python-openxml/python-docx,2062718,scanny,3403760,python-openxml,closed,Feature: Adding picture to table cell,[],[],2,"A perfect use for a tool such as python-docx is to archive a large number of images in an automated fashion.  Unfortunately, floating images is a poor way of doing this and inserting the images in table cells is my preferred route.  I had hoped that python-docx would allow me to do that (and it was, in fact, the only reason I needed it for).  However, it seems to support only floating pictures at this time.  I urge you to consider adding extra functionality to table cells, along the lines of:
