```

FWIW, I'm trying to detect changes to a sonos queue. I can detect these by subscribing to each visible device's avTransport service and testing for events where the change in event.variables can't otherwise be explained. Whenever there is a change in a queue (i.e. a track was added, removed or moved), an event will be sent on the avTransport service of one of the visible devices. However, the event.variables give no indication what the event was. That's my current way of detecting changes in the queue! I was hoping there might be a more direct way of doing this with events.",{},{}
