12111,IssuesEvent,2015-10-15 15:24:16+00:00,37222273,planetlabs/planet-client-python,2676083,geowurster,5247016,planetlabs,opened,Expose intersects parameter in CLI,[],[],0,"It would be nice if the [get scene list](https://www.planet.com/docs/v0/scenes/#get-scene-list) parameters, specifically `intersects`, were exposed in the CLI.  I just had a situation where I wanted to check for scenes intersecting a specific point and had to build an entire GeoJSON file to `$ cat point.geojson | planet search`.  A mild inconvenience, but this would have been much easier:

```
$ planet search --some-flag intersects 'POINT (X Y)'
```",{},{}
