12279,IssuesEvent,2017-07-24 23:26:43+00:00,47576910,googlei18n/fontmake,14880595,robmck-ms,5503833,googlei18n,opened,fontmake ignores --family-name when generating designspace file from Glyphs source,[],[],0,"When generating a designspace file from Glyphs source, fontmake always uses the family name from within the Glyphs file. It ignores if you use --family-name on the commandline. It'd be nice to have it use the same family name so as to be able to control the filename of the designspace file.

Or (maybe better still), a separate commandline parameter for the name of the designspace file. 

My use-case is that I want to build a Makefile that modifies the designspace file after fontmake, but before varLib. To do that, I need to be able to either pass the name into fontmake (e.g. --family-name or some other parameter). ",{},{}
