12355,IssuesEvent,2017-05-30 07:04:59+00:00,3791384,coursera-dl/coursera-dl,340676,balta2ar,5588942,coursera-dl,closed,Add configuration file,"[{'id': 1771895, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/coursera-dl/coursera-dl/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],3,"This is copied from a previous comment of mine on an issue:

---

Regarding your question about `.netrc`, what exactly would you like to specify there? The download method? If yes, then, it would be possible in dirty ways (say, by specifying something like machine name as `coursera-dl-wget`), but that's the _wrong_ way of using `.netrc`: its purpose is to hold authentication data and that only. I would not accept contributions for that.

We may (and _that_ does make sense) use a configuration file to `coursera-dl` where we specify options for how we frequently want `coursera-dl` to be called.

Please file a new issue with a detailed explanation (perhaps cuting and pasting my rationale above) and I may work on that (or accept pull requests that implement that).
",{},{}
