12863,IssuesEvent,2018-08-16 19:11:57+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,38393,msarahan,6392739,conda,opened,conda config for map parameters should allow group operations,[],[],0,"* ``set`` should replace current value with a new list
* ``clear`` or something similar should replace current value with an empty list
* ``extend`` should allow appending more than one value simultaneously",{},{}
12865,IssuesEvent,2018-03-07 09:51:24+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1042804,mingwandroid,6392739,conda,closed,"Use conda and python version instead of ""latest"" in Miniconda installer package, e.g. Miniconda3-4.4.10-py36-Windows-x86_64.exe",[],[],1,"When downloading Miniconda from https://conda.io/miniconda.html the installers are called simply `Miniconda3-latest-Windows-x86_64.exe` or `Miniconda3-latest-MacOSX-x86_64.sh`.

The problem is that with `latest`, once downloaded, there is absolutely no indication what `conda` version it is and what Python version it is.

I would suggest you replace `latest` with `<conda-version>-py<python-version>` e.g.:
~~~
Miniconda3-4.4.10-py36-Windows-x86_64.exe
~~~

This would greatly help with installing proper (intended) version and keep track on Conda installers.",{},{}
12871,IssuesEvent,2017-10-07 16:08:26+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,9658723,jmbertoncelli,6392739,conda,opened,conda uninstall r-essential does not remove r-essential,[],[],0,"when running R from within my virtual environment after using conda remove or uninstall  r-essential from my virtual environment  it is still R that has been installed within the virtual environment that is executed!

I did reboot just in case but still the same.

when I run R from outside the virtual environment this is what I get: /usr/lib64/bin/R for R_HOME
when I run R from within the virtual environment this is what I get: /root/miniconda/envs/lib/R/bin/R for R_HOME?????

Thanks in advance for your support.

JM




