---

Hi,

For automation purpose, I want to install a  package (which is not yet available in conda channels) from outside the env with pip, so I tried the following command : 

`sudo -H $(which pip) install --prefix /usr/local/miniconda3/envs/tensorFlow/ gpustat`

It seems to be installing the same files (at the same paths) as `sudo -H $(which pip) install gpustat` from inside the environment.

After some ""digging"", I found that the shebang generated by `pip` from outside the environment does not take the prefix argument into account : 
```
$ head -1 /usr/local/miniconda3/envs/tensorFlow/bin/gpustat 
#!/usr/local/miniconda3/bin/python
```
instead of : 

`#!/usr/local/miniconda3/envs/tensorFlow/bin/python`

What is my `pip` command missing ?
",{},{}
