12915,IssuesEvent,2018-03-08 16:25:08+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,2042971,cav71,6392739,conda,opened,conda fails to parse windows path in the channel list,[],[],0,"Hi,
this is a bug in parsing local repo dirs in the channel list.

This code in conda/common/url.py:
```
@memoize
def urlparse(url):
    if on_win and url.startswith('file:'):
        url.replace('\\', '/')
return parse_url(url)
```
Should be changed into:
```
@memoize
def urlparse(url):
    if on_win and url.startswith('file:'):
        url = url.replace('\\', '/')
return parse_url(url)
```
",{},{}
12922,IssuesEvent,2017-08-23 21:29:25+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1243351,stefanseefeld,6392739,conda,opened,"""invalid credentials"" error in conda after upgrade to version 4.3.25",[],[],0,"I'm observing an exception involving 
```
requests.exceptions.HTTPError: 401 Client Error: UNAUTHORIZED for url: https://conda.anaconda.org/t/<TOKEN>/r/win-64/repodata.json
```
when running `conda install ...` commands (even when no private channels are involved at all).
If been seeing this on different Windows 64 machines (starting on a build server, then on my own local VM.
Note that I started by installing an official Miniconda3, at which point everything worked fine. Only after I ran `conda install conda` to upgrade to the latest (to work around another conda bug) did the above error start to occur. The current conda version is 4.3.25
",{},{}
