12931,IssuesEvent,2017-10-25 21:46:14+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,closed,LinkError openssl conda env python 2.7 ubuntu linux 32 bit ,[],[],7,"Dear, 

I am attempting to make a new conda env (OS: ubuntu 14.04) with the requirement of using python 2.7, 32 bit. 

To force conda to use 32 bit, I've set the following environment: 
`
export CONDA_FORCE_32BIT=1 
`
which, it appears works: 
`
tomas@PowerEdge-T130:~$ conda info | grep platform                
`
`platform : linux-32
`

Unfortunately, then making a new environment fails: 
`
tomas@PowerEdge-T130:~$ conda create -n myenv python=2.7
Fetching package metadata .........
Solving package specifications: .

Package plan for installation in environment /home/tomas/miniconda3/envs/myenv:

The following NEW packages will be INSTALLED:

    certifi:    2016.2.28-py27_0
    openssl:    1.0.2l-0
    pip:        9.0.1-py27_1
    python:     2.7.13-0
    readline:   6.2-2
    setuptools: 36.4.0-py27_1
    sqlite:     3.13.0-0
    tk:         8.5.18-0
    wheel:      0.29.0-py27_0
    zlib:       1.2.11-0

Proceed ([y]/n)? y

ERROR conda.core.link:_execute_actions(337): An error occurred while installing package 'defaults::openssl-1.0.2l-0'.
LinkError: post-link failed for: defaults::openssl-1.0.2l-0
Attempting to roll back.


LinkError: post-link failed for: defaults::openssl-1.0.2l-0
`

Many posts with similar errors report that the path should not have any 'bang' characters, however, this does not seem to be the case here. Any help on this issue is warmly welcomed. 

Thanks in advance! ",{},{}
