13518,IssuesEvent,2018-01-22 10:31:49+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,14069404,hubo1016,7049303,aio-libs,opened,support reuse_port option when creating server,[],[],0,"Python supports `reuse_port` socket option when creating server

https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-eventloop.html#asyncio.AbstractEventLoop.create_server

With reuse_port you can start multiple processes binding with the same port, easily creating a load-balanced server. While it is possible to start each process on different port, it can be done much easier with `reuse_port` option.",{},{}
13524,IssuesEvent,2017-03-25 19:59:28+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,141546,jwilk,7049303,aio-libs,opened,obsolete reference to WSClientDisconnectedError,[],[],0,"## Long story short

`docs/web_reference.rst` contains this line:

```
      :raise: :exc:`~aiohttp.errors.WSClientDisconnectedError` on closing.
```

But `WSClientDisconnectedError` has been removed in v1.1.0.

## Your environment

