13665,IssuesEvent,2017-05-31 23:58:35+00:00,23984796,jupyter/nbgrader,83444,jhamrick,7388996,jupyter,closed,Assignment List extension is slow,"[{'id': 195882574, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jupyter/nbgrader/labels/refactor', 'name': 'refactor', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}]",[],3,"The reason is because it actually has to shell out to the command line apps rather than running them in the same python session, and the reason it can't run them in the same python session is because the `NotebookApp` and `NbGrader` both inherit from `JupyterApp` which is a singleton, so it raises an error if you try to instantiate `NbGrader` within the `NotebookApp`. Fixing this would require a fair bit of refactoring: moving the bulk of the transfer apps into separate classes that are not subclasses of `JupyterApp`, and then having the apps themselves create those classes and call them (similarly to how the preprocessors work in nbconvert).",{},{}
