14259,IssuesEvent,2018-05-09 19:44:08+00:00,53977862,PyCQA/flake8-bugbear,252209,mxr,8749848,PyCQA,opened,"B301 gives a false positive for pandas DataFrames, Series and Panels",[],[],0,"`iteritems` is a valid function for pandas DataFrames, Series, etc (see docs [here](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/version/0.17.0/generated/pandas.DataFrame.iteritems.html#pandas.DataFrame.iteritems)). However `flake8-bugbear` flags uses of this function:

```
$ cat example.py
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({""A"": [1, 2, 3], ""B"": [4, 5, 6]})
print(list(df.iteritems()))
$ flake8 example.py
example.py:4:12: B301 Python 3 does not include `.iter*` methods on dictionaries. Remove the `iter` prefix from the method name. For Python 2 compatibility, prefer the Python 3 equivalent unless you expect the size of the container to be large or unbounded. Then use `six.iter*` or `future.utils.iter*`.
```

My environment:

```
$ python --version
Python 3.6.5
$ flake8 --version
3.5.0 (flake8-bugbear: 18.2.0, mccabe: 0.6.1, pycodestyle: 2.3.1, pyflakes: 1.6.0) CPython 3.6.5 on Darwin
```",{},{}
14260,IssuesEvent,2017-12-08 19:26:41+00:00,17799097,PyCQA/flake8-import-order,1391482,pgjones,8749848,PyCQA,closed,I202 errors for multiline imports,[],[],3,"The following snippet triggers an I202 error:

```python
from .foo import (
    bar,
    baz,
)

from .zoo import (
    mux,
    mox,
)
```

I think that a blank line should be allowed when a single import spans multiple lines.",{},{}
14262,IssuesEvent,2015-07-16 19:49:28+00:00,27888295,SatelliteQE/nailgun,48132,elyezer,8754276,SatelliteQE,opened,"Should entities raise an exception when assign OneTo{One,Many} fields with a different type?","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/SatelliteQE/nailgun/labels/research', 'name': 'research', 'color': '207de5'}]",[],0,"I'm creating this to collect information about what the action NailGun should take when assigning a different type from the expected one for OneTo{One,Many} fields.

As we may want to do negative tests one would want to assign a not valid entity, should its id be get or an exception be raised? Actually from the Satellite side, if it receives an id it will try to get from the right type table and may work if that id already exists on the right type table.

I'm more in favor of raising an exception because doing a negative test will not bring much benefit as we may get a false negative.",{},{}
14285,IssuesEvent,2017-12-06 20:15:43+00:00,24245737,projectmesa/mesa,10428066,TaylorMutch,8754505,projectmesa,closed,Slider Bar Visualization is not working,"[{'id': 130962365, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/projectmesa/mesa/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],11,"Hello - I've copied the code from the advanced tutorial associated with adding an interactive parameter, but when I run the visualization, the ""Number of Agents"" slider does not appear.  The tutorial does not explicitly say where the UserSettableParameter() should be defined, but I'm assuming it is defined in the server.py file so that it can be passed as a model parameter.  Is there anything else that I might be missing, or anything that might prevent the slider from showing up?  

If it helps, I also tried adjusting the starting value of the slider, and even though I can't see it in the visualization, it seems to have the expected effect on the simulation run.",{},{}
14286,IssuesEvent,2015-02-20 15:21:21+00:00,24245737,projectmesa/mesa,596978,dmasad,8754505,projectmesa,opened,Improve Grid code,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/projectmesa/mesa/labels/Feature', 'name': 'Feature', 'color': '0052cc'}]",[],0,"Gene Callahan (@gcallah) made some good suggestions on streamlining the Grid code on the listserv, which should be integrated.",{},{}
14294,IssuesEvent,2018-05-16 06:09:07+00:00,24245737,projectmesa/mesa,26409057,sivogel,8754505,projectmesa,opened,Independent StagedActivation for different agents? ,[],[],0,"Dear all,

I currently try to rewrite a NetLogo model with Mesa in Python. So far it works quite well but I have issues with the runtime.
My Setup:
I have to types of agents (seeds and plants). Now I want first to run through all seeds than to runs through all plants and within I want to do some changes on the grid.
My current solution:
At the moment I do this by StagedActivation, but this means I always have to loop over all agents, which takes a lot of time. 
My question: 
Is there any option I overlooked to have several different steps or a stages which do not loop over all agents but only over an agent group?

Thanks for help,

Simone",{},{}
