14431,IssuesEvent,2017-04-23 15:47:59+00:00,1151051,django-oscar/django-oscar,2776878,okfish,9057806,django-oscar,opened,CatalogueImportError will never being raised during catalogue import,[],[],0,"So, this code https://github.com/django-oscar/django-oscar/blob/master/src/oscar/management/commands/oscar_import_catalogue.py#L41 will never executed, because `CatalogueImportError` exception class didn't even imported in the `partner.importer` module. Instead of this, `ImportingError` used, but there are no places where it can be caught. 

