14432,IssuesEvent,2016-08-09 03:06:01+00:00,1151051,django-oscar/django-oscar,5034215,SalahAdDin,9057806,django-oscar,opened,Sorl-thumbnail features unnused.,[],[],0,"Hi guys

I worked in a news website using `sorl-thumbnail` package for handle images and i can remember use an admin mixin for improve the admin.

```bash
from sorl.thumbnail.admin import AdminImageMixin

class MyModelAdmin(AdminImageMixin, admin.ModelAdmin):
    pass
```

You can read documentation about [`AdminMixin`](http://sorl-thumbnail.readthedocs.io/en/latest/examples.html#admin-examples).

This feature improve a thumbnail inside model object change form and model object list, yes, you can see the image in the change form and view a small image by each objects in the list.

So, i try use it:
```python
class ProductImageAdmin(AdminImageMixin, admin.ModelAdmin):
    list_display = ['product', 'original', 'display_order', 'date_created']

admin.site.register(ProductImage, ProductImageAdmin)
```

But i couldn't see any change in admin view, so, i investigate in the code and i found this:
```python

    original = models.ImageField(
        _(""Original""), upload_to=settings.OSCAR_IMAGE_FOLDER, max_length=255)
```

In `ProductImage` model Oscar use a normal image field instead a `sorl-thumbnail` [Image Field](http://sorl-thumbnail.readthedocs.io/en/latest/examples.html#model-examples),  for this reason the mixin doesn't works.

But, i think that Oscar use `sorl-thumbnail` for use his Image Field, but seems isn't it.

Have you plans use full featured `sorl-thumbnail`?

Thanks.",{},{}
14434,IssuesEvent,2015-05-23 10:20:33+00:00,1151051,django-oscar/django-oscar,55558,digicase,9057806,django-oscar,opened,Creating a new product via the dashboard causes NoReverseMatch expection,[],[],0,"Looks like it could be because of line 240 of the dashboard/catalogue/product_update.html template:

    {% with children=product.children.all %}

children is NULL as there is no product, however later on in the template the `{% if children %}` tag thinks there are four children. This causes a NoReverseMatch exception for the Edit and Delete button URLs.",{},{}
