14705,IssuesEvent,2016-03-14 23:42:36+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,1377457,pganssle,9849410,dateutil,closed,_isdst() returns different values..,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/time%20zones', 'name': 'time zones', 'color': 'c7def8'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/wontfix', 'name': 'wontfix', 'color': 'ffffff'}]",[],2,"...depending on if its a `tz` or `tzwin` object
```python
from datetime import datetime
from dateutil import tz

now = datetime.now()

tzl = tz.tzlocal()
tzwl = tz.tzwinlocal()

print(tzl._isdst(now), tzwl._isdst(now))
# 0 False
```
Now granted those are protected methods, but you would assume that those would return the same types of values.",{},{}
