14736,IssuesEvent,2017-09-25 17:38:20+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,29159589,chstem,9887454,LonamiWebs,closed, Invalid connection mode on connect(),[],[],2,"I get the following error when trying to connect:

```
    client.connect()

  File ""/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/telethon/telegram_client.py"", line 174, in connect
    ok = super().connect(exported_auth=exported_auth)

  File ""/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/telethon/telegram_bare_client.py"", line 118, in connect
    authenticator.do_authentication(self._sender.connection)

  File ""/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/telethon/network/authenticator.py"", line 22, in do_authentication
    return _do_authentication(connection)

  File ""/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/telethon/network/authenticator.py"", line 41, in _do_authentication
    sender.send(writer.get_bytes())

  File ""/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/telethon/network/mtproto_plain_sender.py"", line 35, in send
    self._connection.send(packet)

  File ""/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/telethon/network/connection.py"", line 172, in send
    raise ValueError('Invalid connection mode specified: ' + str(self._mode))

ValueError: Invalid connection mode specified: None
```

This happens since  `0.13` and only in connection with [PyOtherSide](https://github.com/thp/pyotherside).

I am not sure where this is coming from, but here is my first guess: PyOtherSide executes the imported Python in a separate thread. This might have some unexpected side effects for Telethon?

What are the technical changes from `0.12` to `0.13` with respect to connecting, that might be relevant here?
",{},{}
