14780,IssuesEvent,2018-04-01 14:35:17+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,15344581,expectocode,9887454,LonamiWebs,opened,Calling client.get_input_entity(marked_peer_id) fails if the relevant peer is not in the most recent 100 peers.,[],[],0,"[This line](https://github.com/LonamiWebs/Telethon/blob/898e550335b9979a131dd956c8aa26a01d341b4c/telethon/telegram_client.py#L2460) causes this issue.

Potential fixes: 
- (async only) Change the iter_dialogs(100) to iter_dialogs(limit=None) so that all the dialogs are tried rather than only the first 100, without losing efficiency for the first 100 thanks to async iterators.
- Change the TypeError on this failure path to a ValueError or something else, so that users can try-catch this code without also catching the **real** TypeErrors elsewhere in this function.",{},{}
