14872,IssuesEvent,2018-08-27 14:14:27+00:00,84609153,descarteslabs/descarteslabs-python,3392975,justinwp,10055430,descarteslabs,closed,Issue running sample code for new installs of Shapely and Cartopy,[],[],2,"There is an incompatibility issue between Shapely and Cartopy that has been documented in [Cartopy Issue #805](https://github.com/SciTools/cartopy/issues/805).  Unless you are really lucky to have installed the exact right version of GEOS, cartopy will say `Assertion failed: (0 != cs), function GEOSCoordSeq_getSize_r, file geos_ts_c.cpp, line 3612.` 

Also, if you follow one of the suggestions of 

`pip install shapely cartopy --no-binary shapely --no-binary cartopy` 

(as described in [#783](https://github.com/SciTools/cartopy/issues/738) you will get a segmentation fault.

In order to run the demo code, can you suggest any alternatives to cartopy?  ",{},{}
