15262,IssuesEvent,2016-01-22 16:44:17+00:00,21987374,django-json-api/django-rest-framework-json-api,322706,jerel,11215076,django-json-api,closed,"Set custom ""type"" for ResourceRelatedField",[],[],2,"Hi, all! 
I have the following Django model:
```python
class Comment(model.Model):
    text = models.TextField()
    parent_comment = models.ForeignKey('self', null=True, blank=True, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
```
I want to be able to obtain a list of comments with ""parent"" in relationships, for example:
```javascript
{
  ""data"": [
    {
       ""type"": ""comments"",
        ""id"": ""1"",
        ""attributes"": {
          ""text"": ""First comment""
        },
        ""relationships"": {
          ""parent"": {
            ""data"": null
          } 
        }
    },
    {
       ""type"": ""comments"",
        ""id"": ""2"",
        ""attributes"": {
          ""text"": ""Child comment""
        },
        ""relationships"": {
          ""parent"": {
            ""data"": {
              ""type"": ""comments"",
              ""id"": 1
            }
          } 
        }
    },
  ]
}
```

My serializer:
```python
class CommentSerializer(ModelSerializer):
    parent = ResourceRelatedField(source='parent_comment', read_only=True)

    class Meta:
        model = Comment
        fields = ('text', 'parent',)
```
In my ViewSet I have defined resource_name = 'comments', but it is doesn't work for ""parent"" in relationships. At the present time, ""type"" of ""parent"" is ""Comment"". How can I fix this issue?
",{},{}
