17011,IssuesEvent,2018-07-29 14:12:54+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,4587007,pasbi,17565521,pybind,opened,Crash when importing torch,[],[],0,"## Issue description
Crash when `pybind11::scoped_interpreter` is destructed after importing `torch`.

## Reproducible example code
```
#include <pybind11/embed.h>

int main()
{
  pybind11::scoped_interpreter guard{};
  pybind11::exec(""import torch"");
  // pybind11::module::import(""torch""); // same problem
}
```
Note that the import itself works like a charm.
In the real code, I am using torch and it does what it is supposed to do.
The crash occurs when `guard` goes out of scope, i.e., when it is destructed.

I guess it's a double-free issue, however, I can't narrow down the problem in `torch` as it happens somewhere in its C-implementation.
I already asked in the [gitter lobby](https://gitter.im/pybind/Lobby), but I didn't get an answer.
",{},{}
17012,IssuesEvent,2018-02-19 15:08:27+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,894236,BorisSchaeling,17565521,pybind,opened,"Class with deleted ""operator delete"" and std::unique_ptr<..., nodelete>",[],[],0,"Is this code supposed to compile? 

