This is the VS2017 compile error: 

> include\pybind11\pybind11.h(986): error C2280: 'void S::operator delete(void *)': attempting to reference a deleted function

Line 986 in pybind11.h refers to one of the call_operator_delete() functions. All call_operator_delete() functions expect to be able to call ""operator delete"". It's not surprising that this doesn't work in the example above as ""operator delete"" has been deleted. But as the example does compile with g++ and clang and as I use pybind11::nodelete, I would assume something else goes wrong and VS2017 should actually never try to use those call_operator_delete() functions?",{},{}
