17300,IssuesEvent,2018-01-08 06:47:24+00:00,59214089,SCIP-Interfaces/PySCIPOpt,1506995,mattmilten,19473229,SCIP-Interfaces,closed,Less than or equal constraint on binary variables gets changed into equality constraint,[],[],3,"Here is a minimal example of what I have been debugging throughout the last few hours.
max x + y
s.t. x - 2*y <= 0
x,y \in {0,1}

To me, it seems that x=y=1 is a feasible solution with objective function value 2.
Solving this directly results in x=y=0 as proclaimed optimal solution.
Further, when explicitely providing the correct solution I get an error that it is infeasible (because the inequality constraint is turned into an equality constraint!)

```python
from pyscipopt import Model

model = Model( ""Minimum viable problem"" )
model.setMaximize()
x = model.addVar( vtype=""BINARY"", name=""x"", obj=1 )
y = model.addVar( vtype=""BINARY"", name=""y"", obj=1 )
model.addCons( x - 2 * y <= 0 )

model.printVersion()
