17332,IssuesEvent,2017-04-06 11:34:24+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Protocol: Don't resend acknowledged messages,[],[],0,"## Problem Definition

Raiden has a hard requirement that every mediated message must use a unique non-predictable secret for the transfer at hand, this implies that hashlocks are unique and so are the messages `MediatedTransfer`, `RefundTransfer`, `SecretRequests`, and `Secret`. Since the effect of sending any of these messages is non-revertible, adding the same message into the protocol queue is redundant an unnecessary.

With that in mind, we can use this property as a means to prevent amplification at the protocol layer. For the current HEAD commit e55b2dc917ce389fed773adacc04f61efc5ca6fe, everytime a [Secret message is received](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/e55b2dc917ce389fed773adacc04f61efc5ca6fe/raiden/raiden_service.py#L692-L710) the secret is registered and [SecretReveal](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/e55b2dc917ce389fed773adacc04f61efc5ca6fe/raiden/tokenmanager.py#L159-L181) are sent for each channel that hashlock registered.

## Tasklist

- [ ] List messages types that are unique (e.g. Ping / Pong are not)
- [ ] Update the protocol layer to ignore the same message:

```
add_message(M):
  if M is of a type that is unique: 
    if M in queue: ignore
    if M was sent and acknowledged: ignore
```",{},{}
17343,IssuesEvent,2018-08-16 11:29:41+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,587021,andrevmatos,19666847,raiden-network,opened,WebUI must handle token decimals,"[{'id': 318426947, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMTg0MjY5NDc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 977290049, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NzcyOTAwNDk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/ui', 'name': 'ui', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'kelsos', 'id': 2269732, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjIyNjk3MzI=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/2269732?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/kelsos', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kelsos/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"## Problem Definition

Right now, webUI shows tokens as Raiden sees it: only token `wei`s, as integers. The webUI/client is responsible for managing token decimals, and should handle it gracefully. Each token contract have a `decimals()` method which returns an integer for the amount of decimals this token is configured with. UI `input type=""number""`s should convert from decimal number to integer before sending the values to the REST API (`raiden_amount = int(input_amount * 10**decimals)`) and prevent user from entering more decimals than token supports, and places where any amount/deposit/balance is displayed should take it into account (`ui_amount = raiden_amount / 10**decimals`). `BigNumber` may be required. `RaidenService` may do it before handling data to the rest of the components.",{},{}
17347,IssuesEvent,2018-08-16 16:46:48+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,closed,Create test for send_queued_messages,"[{'id': 974626989, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NzQ2MjY5ODk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/P2', 'name': 'P2', 'color': '683faf', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'pcppcp', 'id': 6489721, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjY0ODk3MjE=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/6489721?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/pcppcp', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pcppcp/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"### Problem Definition
We got [bitten](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/pull/2140)  [2](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/pull/2145) times by a non-tested [codepath](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/pull/2140#discussion_r209240650) of `send_queued_messages` where arguments to `send_async()` were not correct.


### Task

Create a test for this codepath so that we are covered.",{},{}
17348,IssuesEvent,2017-01-11 14:43:55+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1026799,czepluch,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Use mapping for `assets` instead of array,[],[],0,"`Registry.sol` currently uses an array to keep track of all registered tokens (https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/441d7637bc89cc7d70c0afa2cc3817b400fe768e/raiden/smart_contracts/Registry.sol#L7). As pointed out in #232 this could be an attack vector, so we should use a mapping instead. 

This is however not as straight forward as it may seem. See #311 and #232 for details on why it is not as simple as it sounds.",{},{}
17358,IssuesEvent,2017-06-29 09:02:17+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Write channel state changes in the WAL,[],[],0,"## Problem Definition

Channel state changes, once implemented also need to be stored in the WAL.

## Solution

As a step towards channel recoverability we need to be able to store the channel state changes of the channel state machine in the WAL so that recovery can happen.

Depends on https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/507

## Tasklist

- [ ] Write the channel state changes in the WAL


",{},{}
