17442,IssuesEvent,2017-02-16 16:59:49+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Interface for job submission on clusters,"[{'id': 325435541, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'gaow', 'id': 917985, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/917985?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/gaow', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'BoPeng', 'id': 9889312, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9889312?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/BoPeng', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"With the completion of #414 (remote execution of tasks), and planned wait feature ( #436) of the sos core, we will need to find a good way to submit jobs on clusters.

I would propose that we make use of the `CONFIG['hosts'][host]` feature to define behavior for each cluster. Something like:

```
hosts:
   cluster:
        address:    address of head node
        path_map:  how to map files
        shared:        shared filesystem, not likely to have one
        send_cmd:  how to send files to cluster, default value should work
        receive_cmd: how to receive files from cluster, default value should work
        execution_cmd:  THIS WOULD NEED SOME THOUGHT
        wait:                False
        status_cmd:      Status checking command
```

Basically, 

1. option `wait` tells SoS that the job would be in waiting status after `sos execute task` returns, which triggers command `sos execute task --no-wait`.
2. option `execution_cmd`. Instead of `ssh head_node sos execute task`, it would be something like `ssh head_node qsub sos execute task`
3. option `status_cmd` would be a command to check status, something like `ssh head_node sos execute task --check-status`

There are two missing pieces here:

1. SoS does not know how to pass resource options to PBS. Something like

```
job_template:  ""#PBS -wall ${_runtime[""wall""]}
```

might do.

2. SoS does not know how to check the status of the job. Supposedly the `qsub` command would return some ID number but there is no general way to perform `--check-status`.",{},{}
