17860,IssuesEvent,2017-09-25 16:12:10+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,1396878,gravyboat,22243823,streamlink,closed,[Feature request]Auto split -o output files after certain time / size reached,[],[],1,"Why is this feature needed:
I frequently use streamlink to record twitch / youtube live channel included esports and regular stream such as cat live cam.
When certain record session is like... 5 hours or longer, the file become incredibly huge. This is bad for moving / categorizing. 
And, the length of the file makes it difficult to seek for later watching.

tl;dr:
It could be very convenient when output file reached specified length / specified file size, it changed its output file name to... say, 2.mp4.

Thank you for your contributing! I love this project.",{},{}
17875,IssuesEvent,2017-09-25 16:13:13+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,1396878,gravyboat,22243823,streamlink,closed,Streamlink add to previously recorded stream with same name,"[{'id': 592463733, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/streamlink/streamlink/labels/feature%20request', 'name': 'feature request', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}]",[],4,"- [x] This is a feature request.

When a stream ends, I believe it would be a nice addition to have an ""add to"" option added to the rewrite options; or to have an ""add to"" stream flag.

`[cli][info] Opening stream: 720p60 (hls)
File test.mp4 already exists! Overwrite it? [y/N] `
and instead add to that something like 
`File test.mp4 already exists! Overwrite it or add to it? [y/n/a]`

Or if this suggestion is not liked, then if it's possible it would be nice to have a flag that allows adding to previously cut off streams. 

",{},{}
