17950,IssuesEvent,2017-08-16 23:36:57+00:00,94917848,jupyterlab/jupyterlab-git,13174154,ashutoshbondre,22800682,jupyterlab,closed,Prompt User to commit changes after a pull,[],[],3,"We have made the `git pull` command as `git pull upstream master --no-commit` , which means user can pull the changes,but those changes are not automatically committed. As good practice, we should ask the user to commit those pulled changes. 

Also another reason to prompt the commit is, user WILL NOT be able to pull further changes if he/she has not committed previous changes.

