18105,IssuesEvent,2017-06-22 14:24:49+00:00,34138622,jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets,192614,jasongrout,25869250,jupyter-widgets,opened,Output widget module,"[{'id': 207982393, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Right now, the browser Output widget model/view is always patched into the controls module by hand by each manager. This is awkward. The only reason we did this is so that there would be one javascript module name for the entire ipywidgets python package. However, now we don't have that anyway with the base and controls module.

How about we make a new package just for the output widget: `@jupyter-widgets/output` or something. Then each manager just has to look for that specific package and substitute its implementation in, rather than looking for the controls package and then checking the module name. This also lets us treat the controls package like any other package, and not *have* to patch something in.",{},{}
