18239,IssuesEvent,2018-06-20 22:17:42+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,9417701,justinborromeo,28732122,localstack,closed,Kinesis client SdkClientException when using Localstack JUnit test runner with SSL enabled,[],[],0,"I'm writing an integration test for some Kinesis-using code using the Localstack JUnit test runner.  Since the Kinesis Producer Library requires SSL to be enabled, I wrote an environment variable provider that sets the environment variable ""USE_SSL"" to true.  While this allows the KPL code to function properly, I also want to be able to use the KCL to validate that data was added to the stream.  When I use the built-in Docker Kinesis client, I get the following errors:  

`com.amazonaws.SdkClientException: Unable to execute HTTP request: The target server failed to respond` and `Caused by: org.apache.http.NoHttpResponseException: The target server failed to respond`

My test code is as follows:

```
@RunWith(LocalstackDockerTestRunner.class)
@LocalstackDockerProperties(services={""kinesis""}, environmentVariableProvider = LocalstackEnvironmentVariableProvider.class )
public class SomeIT{
    @Test
    public void someTest() throws Exception{
          AmazonKinesis kinesis = DockerTestUtils.getClientKinesis();

          ListStreamsResult streams = kinesis.listStreams();
    }
}
```",{},{}
