18263,IssuesEvent,2018-04-17 08:28:01+00:00,36093931,sentinelsat/sentinelsat,36918467,G00FYDUDE,29057552,sentinelsat,opened,Very slow download,[],[],0,"Hay All,

Just wondering if anyone has been downloading any S2 pre sep 2016 images recently when there are multiple scenes in the granule and the total file size is around 6-7G. When downloading these I very seldom get the normal 2-3MB/s I have one now which has been downloading for 17h so far at 12KB/s its just over 50% done but when I use the direct link i have pulled the same file in 18mins (751ef4c1-f221-4285-8d76-9269cf7a00a2). The same is true for another computer I tested very very slow via sentinelsat but other methods are around the normal speed.
Prior to this I have downloaded thousands of images via sentinel sat but as I have worked back through the sentinel S2 archive it has got slower and slower to download (i don't know much about this is there a cache that builds up and needs emptying or something). 
Does anyone have any thoughts or experienced similar? 

Pc windows 10 and tested on 7 using sentinelsat 0.12.1",{},{}
18266,IssuesEvent,2018-05-08 13:13:28+00:00,36093931,sentinelsat/sentinelsat,1621864,Fernerkundung,29057552,sentinelsat,closed,Failing tests due to Pandas not supporting Python <3.5,[],[],1,"Currently our tests for Python 3.4 fail due to Pandas only being available for Python 2.7, 3.5 and 3.6 ( [source](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/install.html#python-version-support)).

I propose we skip the Pandas/GeoPandas tests for Python <3.5 as it is an optional dependency and the core of `sentinelsat` works fine with Python 3.3-3.6.",{},{}
