18274,IssuesEvent,2017-07-12 11:00:27+00:00,10744270,capnproto/pycapnp,6421750,lucas-sonnabend,29186932,capnproto,opened,unused _DynamicStructReader are hanging around,[],[],0,"Assume I have a proto message like this
```
struct SomeMessage {
    subMessage @0 :SomeSubMessage;
}
struct SomeSubMessage {
    resource @0 :Resource; 
}
```
My program stores the _DynamicStructReader for the resource struct. Because this has a pointer to it's parent I also have the readers of SomeSubMessage and SomeMessage, and it's parent, a _FlatArrayMessage are still hanging around although none of them are needed any more.

I have a branch were I deleted the _parent field of the _DynamicStructReader class, I haven't tested it thoroughly yet, but I can create a pull request soon, if you'd like to

This might be related to #141 but I am not entirely sure. The hypothesis is that because the readers all have cyclic dependencies none of them ever get deleted as long as a single message is still referenced.",{},{}
