18456,IssuesEvent,2018-05-24 13:29:21+00:00,103242244,user-cont/conu,1662493,TomasTomecek,35456931,user-cont,opened,figure out API versioning,"[{'id': 690093571, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/user-cont/conu/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 777487286, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/user-cont/conu/labels/user%20experience', 'name': 'user experience', 'color': '8be567', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Since we introduce a breaking change from time to time, ideally we should be able to provide a way for our users to pick a version of API. Obviously we are limited here python language (function arguments, function names etc.).

